<br>
Personally, to me, all that is different in PvP is that your opponent is smarter than the AI in PvE.  Humans are craftier and tends to use exploits to their advantage.  It's human vs human, brain vs brain.  <br>
<br>
Say for example, you're playing Madden 2002 on your Playstation 2 against the computer.  You might not win on the first try, but eventually you will learn the tricks that the computer is programmed to do, you use it to your benefit and to help you win.  However, if you play it against your friend, he/she is always liable to make a move you do not, and cannot expect.  I surely wouldn't expect game designers to design whole new mechanics for football so I can play Madden 2002 against my RL buddy. Whoever wins in a PvP situation is purely based on skills and strategy, not merely on a prediction of how tough you expect your opponent to be.  If you can't out wit another human it's your own lack of skill or stupidity. Why should game designers create a whole new aspect for you to play in? <p><CENTER>
