<br>
A) Crit hits and does close to max damage<br>
B) The second normal shot hits<br>
C) The 2 combined do enough damage to significantly slow the target down, buying the scout enough time to get off the 3rd shot.<br>
<br>
Now, once the scout is in melee, there's no comparison; the fighter has higher defense, higher attack power, and is basically superior in every way, shape, and form.<br>
<br>
So why, exactly, should a scout not be more accurate than a fighter? The scout -has- to land those few vital shots at long range, he can't just wait a second and get another chance, and even if he could, he doesn't have the defensive skills to last that long, plus, the bow is virtually useless at short range.<br>
<br>
That is why scouts -should- be more accurate: it's as much fitting for the class as it is a necessity. Either that, or we should nerf fighters: they're only allowed to swing 3 times with their specced weapon (which will cost them a little in excess of 1sp per swing), then have to take off their armor and use the weapon they're least proficient with.<br>
...and as for that argument about archers soloing reds, that's BS... there's 1 situation I know of where that's possible (rangers vs. those tree things around level 8), where I see those neo-dr00d theurgusts regularly soloing yellow and oranges without breaking a sweat, while I struggle to take a blue. If anything needs to be &quot;fixed,&quot; it's the casters in PvE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umacnat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macnat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hem1.passagen.se/lonnelid/english.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 4:24:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Now, once the scout is in melee, there's no comparison; the fighter has higher defense, higher attack power, and is basically superior in every way, shape, and form.&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
