Hmm, never thought of it that way... Right now with my base setup, I was going to max bow, skip celtic dual and get blades to 39...  If I were to limit both bow and blade to 39ish, I could spec up both stealth and pathfinding to about equivelant levels. (still going to skip Celtic Dual)<br>
<br>
<b><br>
Third, I am not sure why archers continue to fully spec stealth either. Stealth is based on both distance and spec level. The further away you are the lower the spec level you need to remain completely invisible. The higher spec you go in stealth allows you to get closer to your target without becoming visible. So the $64 question is, why do archers think they need to get so close to the target? </b><br>
<br>
Heheh, you've got it backwards... High stealth, while nice for running between targets, is really an advantage when running <I>away</I> from targets...  The higher your stealth spec, the less of a distance you need between yourself and that big ugly troll chasing after you before you can restealth...<br>
