Macnat - <br>
You're still looking at archers like they're intended to be half-arsed tanks. No Hunter that wants to be a sniper archer is going to spec Beastcraft for the pet; it'd be pretty damn hard to hide with a pet around. I'm sure it'd be great for PvE, but more of a detriment in RvR than anything else. Besides, it's to my understanding that Hunters have melee skills that are significantly superior to Rangers and Scouts. <br>
<br>
You just seem to have this idea that archers are in dire need of bow nerfing and should elect to neglect their bow skills to build up others, which is pointless, really. There's a reason I keep bringing up the second-tier fighter argument: if archers aren't better with a bow than everyone else and can't spec it very highly and have a payoff for doing so, there's virtually no point in playing an archer over any other class capable of using a bow. In it's simplest terms, my argument is that the big draw for archer classes is archery; don't take that away from us. If we wanted to be a melee class that can use a bow, well... there's already several of those. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaurincotg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saurin CoTG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/27/01 8:36:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> I understand, at least in part your point, however, you have to realize that even with NO training in bow an archer class is better at archery than every other class.  The bow types alone are superior to anything that a melee class can use.  Above and beyond that, once you get critical shot 1, the disparity only widens from there.   Consequently, I just don't buy into the argument that if you don't fully spec your bow, you might as well play a melee class with a bow.  <br>
