<br>
Keep in mind that with bow spec, you can't just stand there and repeatedly fire. It takes time to fire off shots. In PvE, you get 3 if you're lucky. In RvR, you're currently the most widely hated enemy on the battlefield and your expected lifespan drops dramatically if you're found.<br>
<br>
Because of this, the reason scouts can spec melee skills is out of necessity. Mythic didn't make the bow powerful enough to kill at a range dependably (against a roughly equal target), so archers have to melee, and we aren't nearly as proficient as a dedicated tank. Conversely, a merc can fire his crossbow at a target to get a little bonus damage before the fight starts, then deliver a serious beatdown at close range. He has defensive skills, better armor, better melee skills, and in general has a much higher survivability rate if that ranged shot misses. <br>
<br>
I'm beginning to feel redundant... the short of my point, sort of an addendum to my previous post, is that archers only get a few shots, and missing 1 out of 3 shots is potentially devastating to a scout while to a melee, it's not a big deal. Archers NEED those few shots. Regardless of any correlation to the archer's basis IRL, from a gameplay standpoint, archers really should be more accurate. I don't want to seem as if I'm complaining about damage; I'm not at all, just accuracy. We've already got to cope with other class' defensive skills that are far more devastating to archers than other classes (i.e. bladeturn and engage), just let us have our accuracy back.<br>
<br>
Besides... IRL I'm into archery as a hobby, and I'm a better shot than my level 12 scout. =P You'd think the one stemming from the fantasy RPG would be a little better... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiatek2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiatek2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/27/01 3:43:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> maybe you should agree to disagree =) starting to repeat same points =)<br>
